  "text": "Nitric oxide (NO) synthesized in macrophages was quantitated by measuring the level of the nitrite ion (NO 2 -) in the incubation medium [CITATION_1] . The cells were suspended in CM, supplemented with 50 U/ml IFN-γ and 100 ng/ml LPS and incubated for 48 h in SC; eight samples were taken for each in vitro experimental group. After that, 100 μl of the supernatant was mixed with 100 μl of the Griess reagent and kept in the dark for 10 min at room temperature (RT). Absorbance at 540 nm was then measured using the SpectraCount TM microplate reader (Canberra Packard).",
